Interface SerializableLambda

  • All Superinterfaces:
    java.io.Serializable
    All Known Subinterfaces:
    Cb<T>, CbBundle<T>, CbBundleComponent<T>, CbComponent<T>, CbConfiguration<T,U>, CbConfigurationComponent<T,U>, CbDictionary<T>, CbDictionaryComponent<T>, CbFuture<T,F>, CbRefServiceRefService<T,S>, CbRefServiceRefServiceComponent<T,S>, CbService<T,S>, CbServiceComponent<T,S>, CbServiceComponentRef<T,S>, CbServiceDict<T,S>, CbServiceMap<T,S>, CbServiceRef<T,S>, CbServiceService<T,S>, CbServiceServiceComponent<T,S>, FluentProperty, InstanceCbBundle, InstanceCbConfiguration<T>, InstanceCbConfigurationComponent<T>, InstanceCbServiceService<S>, InstanceCbServiceServiceComponent<S>

    public interface SerializableLambda
extends java.io.Serializable
    Base interface for serializable lambdas. Some lambda must be serializable in order to allow to introspect their type and method signatures.
